===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|かん|ateji=y|yomi=o|alt=鑵,カン}}
Likely from {{bor|ja|nl|kan||cylindrical metallic container|sort=かん}}, with additional influence from {{cog|en|can||cylindrical metallic container|sort=かん}}. The kanji is an example of {{ja-ateji}}. Alternatively, from {{der|ja|ltc|-|sort=かん}} {{m|zh|罐|tr=kuɑnH||can; jar; tin}}. The usage of {{m|ja|缶}} is likely due to a {{m|ja|新字体|tr=[[shinjitai]]}} simplification from earlier {{m|ja|旧字体|tr=[[kyūjitai]]}} {{m|ja|罐}}, where the phonetic component {{m|ja|雚}} was entirely eliminated.

